14:59.691 --> 15:01.067
(Sighing)

15:01.192 --> 15:02.861
<i>Can you tell your monkey here</i>

15:02.986 --> 15:05.697
<i>that he only needs to hit me
if I won't talk?</i>

15:05.822 --> 15:07.866
<i>He doesn't seem to understand the rules!</i>

15:15.248 --> 15:18.293
<i>When we got busted last night,
things got crazy.</i>

15:19.586 --> 15:22.172
<i>I managed to disarm one of them
and kidnapped him.</i>

15:22.297 --> 15:25.342
<i>- He made me drive to the Old Port.</i>

15:25.467 --> 15:28.678
<i>I was afraid he was going to kill me
and leave me there.</i>

15:28.803 --> 15:30.388
<i>I braked suddenly,</i>

15:30.513 --> 15:32.641
<i>and he hit the back of the seat.</i>

15:32.766 --> 15:35.518
<i>- I dropped the gun.
Punched him in the head.</i>

15:35.644 --> 15:38.146
<i>He lost control of the truck, and I jumped.</i>

15:38.271 --> 15:39.731
<i>- When I got out of the vehicle,</i>

15:39.856 --> 15:41.650
<i>he was running,
so I shot at him.</i>

15:41.775 --> 15:46.738
<i>- Luckily, he only winged me.
So, I kept on running.</i>

15:47.155 --> 15:49.658
<i>You don't want to know
what my night was like!</i>

15:49.783 --> 15:52.160
(Chuckling)
- No, I'm dying to know.

15:54.788 --> 15:56.998
Seriously, I'm curious.

15:58.667 --> 16:01.628
<i>- I didn't want to take a chance
by going somewhere and getting pinched,</i>

16:01.753 --> 16:03.964
<i>so I spent the night outside.</i>

16:05.256 --> 16:07.258
<i>I stole a hoodie off a bum,</i>

16:07.384 --> 16:11.262
<i>pounded a few cups of coffee,
'cause I knew it'd be a long night.</i>

16:11.805 --> 16:13.723
<i>I made myself a nice Band-Aid
with some napkins.</i>

16:13.848 --> 16:16.476
<i>All I could find for the pain
was some ecstasy.</i>

16:16.810 --> 16:18.228
That's it.

16:18.353 --> 16:19.604
<i>- You're a hero!</i>

16:20.355 --> 16:22.107
<i>When I first saw you,</i>

16:22.524 --> 16:24.943
<i>I thought,
"Here's just another Anglo,"</i>

16:25.068 --> 16:27.112
<i>but you're much more than that.</i>

16:28.238 --> 16:29.656
<i>- Thank you.</i>

16:30.323 --> 16:33.284
<i>- This is the composite sketch
of the scumbag.</i>

16:33.702 --> 16:38.581
<i>If you see him, call my voicemail
and leave it a message.</i>

16:38.707 --> 16:39.958
<i>10-4!</i>

16:40.083 --> 16:42.043
(Groaning)

16:42.502 --> 16:44.587
<i>- You little prick!</i>

16:45.547 --> 16:47.215
<i>- Looks real, Boss.</i>

16:47.340 --> 16:49.092
(Groaning)

16:55.140 --> 16:56.808
- Doctor's here?

16:56.933 --> 16:59.269
- Yeah, he's standby.

17:01.354 --> 17:03.189
- Tsk!

17:03.314 --> 17:05.275
Well, go get him.

17:08.028 --> 17:09.404
(Breathing heavily)

17:13.700 --> 17:15.827
- When do you wanna wrap it up?

17:15.952 --> 17:17.119
- I don't.

17:17.244 --> 17:19.372
It can't just look real. It has to be real.

17:19.497 --> 17:21.833
So we follow protocol.
Everything by the book.

17:21.958 --> 17:24.294
There's too much riding on this already.

17:24.419 --> 17:26.253
- So, you really shot your friend?

17:26.378 --> 17:28.173
- Yes, I did.

17:28.298 --> 17:31.092
- Just to be sure, boss,
we're not friends, right?

17:31.217 --> 17:33.344
(All laughing)

17:37.974 --> 17:40.935
<i>- Doc, go easy
when you pull the bandage off.</i>

17:41.061 --> 17:42.729
(Groaning)

17:54.574 --> 17:56.534
What the fuck?

17:56.993 --> 17:58.787
<i>What's he doing with that?</i>

17:58.912 --> 18:00.830
- Hey, hey. Shut up.

18:03.750 --> 18:06.044
(Groaning)

18:16.554 --> 18:17.847
<i>- What's he doing?</i>

18:18.598 --> 18:20.350
(Beeping)

18:22.560 --> 18:25.522
<i>- Loaded with caffeine.
Amphetamines, too.</i>

18:26.147 --> 18:27.107
- Hmm!

18:30.276 --> 18:31.986
<i>- He needs stitches.</i>

18:32.362 --> 18:33.238
- Mike...

18:33.363 --> 18:36.366
Come on, man. Untie him.
Get him a drink. Let's go.

18:40.662 --> 18:42.413
<i>- Thanks, Michel.</i>

18:42.539 --> 18:46.000
<i>- Call me Michel one more time,
and I'll rip your head off.</i>

18:47.627 --> 18:52.715
<i>- Michel, I'll have a scotch
with just one ice cube, please.</i>

18:52.841 --> 18:54.551
(Chuckling)

18:56.010 --> 18:58.179
- Ah! It's good to have you back, Davey.

18:58.304 --> 19:01.724
I don't want you to worry.
The doctor's gonna fix you up.

19:01.850 --> 19:02.934
And here...

19:03.977 --> 19:07.605
Buy yourself some new clothes,
'cause you smell like a homeless hooker.

19:07.730 --> 19:09.107
Your apartment's burned.

19:09.232 --> 19:11.734
So Mikey's gonna set you up
with a room upstairs. Yeah?

19:11.860 --> 19:13.611
<i>- Thanks, you won't regret it.</i>

19:13.736 --> 19:15.905
- Oh, I have no regrets.

19:16.030 --> 19:19.576
It's the people who fuck with me
who have regrets.

19:24.831 --> 19:26.833
<i>- Where's that scotch, Michel?</i>

19:42.932 --> 19:44.893
(Breathing shallowly)

20:05.872 --> 20:07.498
(Sighing)

20:07.624 --> 20:09.918
<i>- It's not the Ritz,
but your neighbours are cute!</i>

20:11.961 --> 20:14.464
<i>After last night,
we're changing things up.</i>

20:14.589 --> 20:18.092
<i>- What do you mean?
- Deliver right to the main garage.</i>

20:18.718 --> 20:20.845
<i>We need 25 cars in 5 days.</i>

20:21.179 --> 20:24.474
<i>- 25 in 5? We just lost half our team!</i>

20:24.599 --> 20:26.809
<i>- I've got new guys starting tonight.</i>

20:26.935 --> 20:28.895
<i>- The deadline is new. What's the deal?</i>

20:29.020 --> 20:31.022
<i>- It's none of your goddamn business!</i>

20:31.147 --> 20:34.025
<i>You're early!
- I'm doing the day shift.</i>

20:34.150 --> 20:35.485
Oh!

20:35.610 --> 20:38.363
<i>I thought no guys
were allowed upstairs!</i>

20:38.488 --> 20:40.240
<i>- He's your roommate for the week.</i>

20:40.990 --> 20:44.744
<i>- You can put him in my room
if he's afraid to sleep alone.</i>

20:44.869 --> 20:46.371
<i>I don't bite.</i>

20:47.747 --> 20:49.874
<i>And I like bad boys!</i>

20:52.460 --> 20:54.379
<i>- Your rockstar suite.</i>

20:54.504 --> 20:55.964
- Wow!

20:56.923 --> 20:59.759
<i>Are you the one I call for room service?</i>

20:59.884 --> 21:01.302
<i>- Don't touch my girls.</i>

21:01.427 --> 21:03.846
<i>You owe me a pickup truck.
I want it by 3:00.</i>

21:03.972 --> 21:05.390
<i>- Are you fucking kidding me?</i>

21:06.516 --> 21:08.017
- Try me.

21:10.478 --> 21:12.438
(Electronics beeping)

21:16.150 --> 21:19.153
(Engine revving,
tires screeching)

21:24.450 --> 21:26.286
- Oh!

21:28.955 --> 21:30.248
You trust him?

21:30.373 --> 21:32.667
- Well, he's one of our best.

21:32.792 --> 21:34.752
- No, that's not what I asked.

21:37.672 --> 21:40.383
- Yeah, I trust him.

21:43.052 --> 21:44.637
- You vouch for him?

21:47.640 --> 21:49.142
- Yes.

21:51.352 --> 21:52.812
- It's on you, then.

22:18.338 --> 22:19.714
- Wow!

22:19.839 --> 22:22.759
You're deep undercover.

22:23.301 --> 22:25.678
<i>- There's no time for your jokes.</i>

22:27.764 --> 22:29.432
- One man...

22:30.933 --> 22:35.730
sacrifices everything
and faces destiny

22:35.855 --> 22:40.735
to clean the filthy business
of the curling world.

22:40.860 --> 22:43.029
He's gonna clean it,

22:43.154 --> 22:46.366
armed with a gun and a broom.

22:46.491 --> 22:49.952
Martin Ward is...

22:51.245 --> 22:52.622
<i>Balls of Stone.</i>

22:52.747 --> 22:54.415
(Snorting)

22:54.540 --> 22:56.209
(Both laughing)

22:58.711 --> 23:00.630
- How's the shoulder?

23:00.755 --> 23:01.798
<i>- It's OK.</i>

23:01.923 --> 23:05.301
<i>You didn't have to go that far,
but it worked. They believed me.</i>

23:05.426 --> 23:08.262
<i>I was scared shitless.
I thought they were going to kill me!</i>

23:08.388 --> 23:09.931
- Hmm...

23:10.056 --> 23:12.350
<i>- And thanks for the composite sketch!</i>

23:12.475 --> 23:14.727
<i>It was so good, I had to...</i>

23:14.852 --> 23:16.312
(Chuckling)

23:19.565 --> 23:21.442
Wow!

23:22.485 --> 23:25.029
<i>Federal gets quite the budget!</i>
- Mm-hmm!

23:25.154 --> 23:27.949
<i>- We'd be two of us in a garden shed
with an iPhone 4.</i>

23:28.074 --> 23:29.492
(Chuckling)

23:29.617 --> 23:31.828
- OK, time to information share.

23:31.953 --> 23:33.996
What do you know about DiPietro?

23:34.122 --> 23:36.833
<i>- He's been working
for the Caprese family forever.</i>

23:36.958 --> 23:38.960
<i>But I was recruited by Mike Dubois.</i>

23:39.085 --> 23:40.753
<i>It's only been three months</i>

23:40.878 --> 23:44.132
<i>since DiPietro showed up
and started running things.</i>

23:44.257 --> 23:46.843
- What we've gathered
is that DiPietro's been sidelined

23:46.968 --> 23:49.804
by the godfather himself,
and he's none too happy about it.

23:49.929 --> 23:52.974
- You think he's ready to flip?
- We hope that's the case, yes.

23:53.099 --> 23:57.270
We squeeze him hard enough,
he gives us everybody at the top of the food chain.

23:57.687 --> 24:01.190
<i>- That's why he wants a side business.</i>
- But it doesn't make any sense.

24:01.315 --> 24:04.610
Why dabble in stolen cars
when there's more money to be had in drugs?

24:04.735 --> 24:08.489
<i>- I tried explaining it to you,
but then you started shooting at me.</i>

24:08.614 --> 24:11.492
<i>They've been talking about
a client for a while.</i>

24:11.617 --> 24:16.038
<i>I don't know what or who it is,
but I know it's big.</i>

24:16.622 --> 24:20.960
<i>The only change is the deadline:
they want 25 cars in 5 days.</i>

24:21.085 --> 24:24.464
<i>And we're not going
to the transit warehouse anymore.</i>

24:24.589 --> 24:28.009
<i>We go straight to the main garage.
Here's the address.</i>

24:30.845 --> 24:33.097
- Well, then, from now on,

24:33.222 --> 24:36.017
I'm gonna be in your head 24/7.

24:36.142 --> 24:39.604
With this little device,
you'll be able to hear me.

24:39.729 --> 24:43.399
If anything goes wrong,
I can be there within minutes.

24:46.611 --> 24:48.112
You put it in your ear.

24:48.237 --> 24:49.906
<i>- I know, but how--</i>

24:50.031 --> 24:52.074
- Turn it on here.
- OK.

24:53.367 --> 24:55.161
<i>And you'll hear me when I talk?</i>

24:55.286 --> 24:56.829
- Oh yes!

24:57.872 --> 24:59.248
- Cool!

25:01.167 --> 25:03.503
(Chuckling)

25:03.628 --> 25:05.922
<i>That was some reunion!</i>

25:06.464 --> 25:09.383
<i>What are the odds that you'd raid
the spot I was working undercover?</i>

25:09.509 --> 25:12.553
- Fairly high, I would imagine,
since our job depends

25:12.678 --> 25:15.223
on being in the wrong place
at the right time.

25:15.348 --> 25:16.307
(Both chuckling)

25:17.975 --> 25:19.977
<i>- And you? How's the family?</i>

25:20.102 --> 25:21.979
- Never better.

25:22.104 --> 25:25.983
My sister married an 86-year-old
somewhat senile banker.

25:26.108 --> 25:28.319
Lives in Switzerland now.

25:28.444 --> 25:29.445
<i>- And Jonathan?</i>

25:29.570 --> 25:32.448
- Your guess is as good as mine.

25:32.573 --> 25:34.742
Last I heard, he was in Montreal.

25:34.867 --> 25:36.327
<i>- You want me to find him?</i>

25:36.452 --> 25:40.540
- Oh, Dave, finding people is easy for me.

25:41.749 --> 25:43.376
Communicating with them,

25:43.501 --> 25:46.170
apparently, I haven't mastered yet.

25:47.755 --> 25:50.800
<i>- Kids aren't easy.</i>

25:52.677 --> 25:55.429
<i>Gabrielle is living
in my old apartment upstairs.</i>

25:55.555 --> 25:56.764
- That's wonderful, no?

25:56.889 --> 25:59.100
<i>- It would be, if it weren't for Cousin Itt.</i>

25:59.225 --> 26:02.228
<i>- Cousin Itt?
- Her boyfriend.</i>

26:02.687 --> 26:05.982
<i>It's like all he does is grow hair.</i>

26:06.399 --> 26:08.442
(Grunting)
(Laughing)

26:09.485 --> 26:12.071
<i>It's hard to tell
if he's speaking or burping.</i>

26:12.196 --> 26:14.782
<i>Gabrielle's good.
She applied to Nicolet.</i>

26:14.907 --> 26:17.785
- The police academy!
- Mm-hmm!

26:18.494 --> 26:19.912
<i>All right, I have to go!</i>

26:20.037 --> 26:23.583
<i>I only have a couple hours to find a pickup truck.</i>
- Well, I'm right behind you.

26:23.708 --> 26:25.876
Don't forget to put your earpiece in.

26:26.002 --> 26:28.045
<i>- So you'll be in my head 24/7?</i>

26:28.170 --> 26:31.132
- Well, I might give you some rest
from time to time,

26:31.257 --> 26:33.551
considering it's been uninhabited for so long.

26:33.676 --> 26:35.428
(Laughing)
- Wow!

26:35.553 --> 26:37.638
<i>The Ontarian grew a sense of humour!</i>

26:37.763 --> 26:40.016
<i>You've changed, man!
I'm worried about you!</i>

26:42.268 --> 26:45.021
<i>- You're full of shit!
That's not Price's truck!</i>

26:45.146 --> 26:47.857
<i>- You don't believe me?
Check out what was inside!</i>

26:50.776 --> 26:51.652
<i>His new mask!</i>

26:53.029 --> 26:55.615
<i>Check it out! It's awesome!</i>

26:56.782 --> 26:58.034
(All laughing)

26:59.952 --> 27:03.706
<i>Price is a man of few words.
Now he'll be speechless for months!</i>

27:03.831 --> 27:05.833
Hey, Mike!

27:05.958 --> 27:07.835
<i>Listen to this! You'll die laughing!</i>

27:07.960 --> 27:11.589
<i>- The whole building heard your story already.
And you'll tell it 40 more times anyway!</i>

27:11.714 --> 27:14.175
- Ah, Mike!
<i>You're a ray of sunshine!</i>

27:14.300 --> 27:16.385
<i>You should do ads for orange juice!</i>

27:17.011 --> 27:20.848
<i>- You have to bring his mask back!
He'll be off his game without it!</i>

27:21.557 --> 27:26.520
<i>- You want me to go up to him
after practice and say:</i>

27:26.646 --> 27:28.230
<i>"Excuse me, Mr. Price.</i>

27:28.356 --> 27:30.900
<i>I stole your truck, and this was inside.</i>

27:31.025 --> 27:35.363
<i>I know goalies are as superstitious
as bingo ladies,</i>

27:35.488 --> 27:38.866
<i>so I brought it back so you don't
end up puking everywhere."</i>

27:39.408 --> 27:41.911
<i>- Put it in the mail.
- I'll bring it to him.</i>

27:43.829 --> 27:46.457
<i>- You think I'd give it to you?
- Sure!</i>

27:46.582 --> 27:49.752
<i>- In two weeks, I'll find it at the flea market!</i>
(Scoffing)

27:50.169 --> 27:52.088
<i>He once sold
his sister's washer and dryer...</i>

27:54.340 --> 27:55.841
<i>for three mags!</i>

27:56.217 --> 27:58.386
<i>What are you gonna do with three mags?</i>

28:01.681 --> 28:03.224
<i>The eyes aren't right.</i>

28:04.392 --> 28:07.228
- And you'd never seen him before?
- First time.

28:07.353 --> 28:09.063
<i>That's good!</i>

28:11.065 --> 28:14.276
<i>I'm sure they were the big clients
I was telling you about.</i>

28:14.402 --> 28:16.987
<i>They were so young, though!
The oldest might've been 25.</i>

28:17.113 --> 28:21.325
- I still can't get my head around this.
Why cars? Why not drugs?

28:21.450 --> 28:25.788
<i>- Because there's a demand!
There's a market for everything.</i>

28:25.913 --> 28:29.417
- You know you can actually buy
clean urine on the Internet?

28:29.542 --> 28:32.962
<i>- Then, I'm surprised there's no
high-school-diploma pushers in Quebec!</i>

28:33.087 --> 28:35.798
(Both chuckling)
- OK, let's find out where they're from.

28:35.923 --> 28:37.967
<i>- Come on, goddammit!</i>

28:38.092 --> 28:41.178
<i>You think you're so cool
with your shitty firewall!</i>

28:41.303 --> 28:43.723
<i>If I shove this up your ass,
what will you do?</i>

28:44.265 --> 28:48.102
<i>- That's MC, our computer whiz.</i>

28:48.227 --> 28:50.271
<i>MC, David.</i>

28:51.147 --> 28:54.442
<i>- Some cowboy move, stealing Price's truck,
but I like your style.</i>

28:55.526 --> 28:59.655
<i>You and me are going to make
a fucking dangerous team!</i>

28:59.780 --> 29:01.532
<i>- A team?
- That's right!</i>

29:01.657 --> 29:04.285
<i>I'm your eyes, your ears,
your hands, your everything!</i>

29:04.410 --> 29:07.037
<i>But what I'm trying to do -</i>

29:07.163 --> 29:09.540
<i>what I will do, goddammit! -</i>

29:09.665 --> 29:12.543
<i>is hack into the system
at the Sopranos' garage.</i>

29:12.918 --> 29:15.296
<i>I can see in that look
you're wondering how, right?</i>

29:15.421 --> 29:17.339
<i>- Oh no. That's not what I'm wondering.</i>

29:17.465 --> 29:21.635
<i>- Who has poles and wires everywhere?
Who?</i>

29:21.761 --> 29:23.804
<i>Bell and Hydro-Québec.</i> Boom!

29:23.929 --> 29:27.224
<i>If I hack into their system and bypass it...</i>

29:29.351 --> 29:32.188
Come on, baby! <i>Allez!</i>

29:32.313 --> 29:35.524
Bang! Yes, fucker!

29:35.649 --> 29:37.109
<i>I've got cameras!</i>

29:38.319 --> 29:41.113
<i>Who's the boss? Who's the genius?</i>

29:42.114 --> 29:45.284
<i>Take that, Steve Jobs!</i>
You wanted a Macintosh?

29:45.409 --> 29:48.662
<i>I'll give you my Macintosh!</i>

29:49.371 --> 29:51.665
<i>Take that!</i>

29:51.791 --> 29:54.376
<i>Oh, yeah, Bill Gates?
You thought you knew everything?</i>

29:54.502 --> 29:57.338
(MC grunting)

29:59.632 --> 30:04.595
<i>All right! Ha ha!
As of now, we're a team!</i>

30:04.720 --> 30:07.723
<i>I need help with the computers.
Their security is tight.</i>

30:07.848 --> 30:09.892
<i>- I don't know anything about computers.</i>

30:10.017 --> 30:14.396
<i>- It's easy. Just take pictures of their system.
- Oh, OK.</i>

30:14.522 --> 30:17.525
<i>- Computers, wiring,
external hard drives, modems...</i>

30:17.650 --> 30:19.360
<i>Whatever you can.</i> Name it.

30:19.485 --> 30:23.697
<i>- Sure. Hello, Minnie Mouse?
I'm undercover, you know.</i>

30:23.823 --> 30:26.492
<i>You think I can walk around
snapping pictures with my phone?</i>

30:26.617 --> 30:28.661
<i>- He's cute. You're cute.</i>

30:32.373 --> 30:33.958
(Exhaling sharply)

30:35.000 --> 30:36.585
(Chuckling)

30:41.340 --> 30:42.925
<i>- I need your help.</i>

30:44.051 --> 30:46.428
<i>Can you get this back to Carey Price?</i>

30:46.554 --> 30:48.639
<i>If they start losing because of it,</i>

30:48.764 --> 30:51.851
<i>the city will go nuts,
and people will lose their jobs!</i>

30:52.518 --> 30:54.144
- Hmm...
- Uh...

30:54.728 --> 30:56.230
<i>Sorry, my mistake.</i>

30:56.355 --> 31:00.109
<i>Leafs fan.
I can't trust you with this!</i>

31:00.234 --> 31:02.069
<i>Is there anyone from Montreal here?</i>

31:03.195 --> 31:04.613
<i>Anyone?</i>

31:08.033 --> 31:10.286
<i>Non, non,</i> fuck you, <i>toi!</i>

31:12.621 --> 31:14.582
(Whispering): Oh wow!

31:22.715 --> 31:24.633
<i>- I can't find the words.</i>

31:25.217 --> 31:29.471
- Really fucking weird, but awesome!

31:30.723 --> 31:32.516
- OK.

31:32.641 --> 31:35.436
- David, your camera's too low. Get it up.

31:38.105 --> 31:38.981
Perfect.

31:39.106 --> 31:40.024
<i>- OK, guys...</i>

31:40.149 --> 31:42.109
I know we're asking a lot here,

31:42.234 --> 31:45.279
but this is your time to step up, make your mark.

31:45.404 --> 31:47.573
<i>To keep you motivated,
Sylvio has doubled everybody's fee.</i>

31:47.698 --> 31:48.365
- Nice!

31:48.490 --> 31:51.118
<i>- If you think you're being followed,
don't come here.</i>

31:51.243 --> 31:55.414
<i>Ditch the car and call me at the bar.
Don't call my cell. Is that clear?</i>

31:55.539 --> 31:56.957
<i>- What if we're arrested?</i>

31:57.082 --> 32:00.836
- OK, look, anything happens to you out there,

32:00.961 --> 32:03.297
<i>I want you to remember I got your bail...</i>

32:03.422 --> 32:04.798
<i>- That's DiPietro.</i>

32:04.924 --> 32:07.217
- ...as long as you keep
your fucking mouth shut.

32:07.343 --> 32:08.802
(Both chuckling)

32:08.928 --> 32:11.639
Now, for those of you
who don't know me well yet,

32:11.764 --> 32:13.474
<i>I'm actually quite a nice guy...</i>

32:14.808 --> 32:15.851
until I'm not.

32:15.976 --> 32:18.020
So, here's what makes me not:

32:18.145 --> 32:22.107
You talk about the job
outside of these 4 walls. Yeah?

32:22.232 --> 32:24.860
You know, you shoot your mouth off

32:24.985 --> 32:27.488
to impress your buddies, get laid, huh?

32:27.613 --> 32:29.198
(Chuckling)

32:29.323 --> 32:33.702
<i>Oh, you know, another thing
that really gets me</i>

32:33.827 --> 32:37.373
<i>is when you don't show your face
when I expect to see it.</i>

32:38.874 --> 32:41.085
<i>- What happens when you're not a nice guy?</i>

32:41.210 --> 32:43.420
(Laughing and stammering)

32:43.545 --> 32:45.631
- Who the fuck is this guy?

32:45.756 --> 32:46.840
(All chuckling)

32:46.966 --> 32:49.009
(Martin): <i>No! No!</i>

32:49.134 --> 32:50.719
Not now, David!

32:55.516 --> 32:56.558
<i>(Man coughing)</i>

32:56.684 --> 32:58.102
(Groaning)

33:05.025 --> 33:06.777
(Man whimpering)

33:06.902 --> 33:08.404
(Panting)

33:08.529 --> 33:10.072
(Laughing)

33:10.489 --> 33:12.741
- Any other questions?

33:12.866 --> 33:14.159
(Man coughing)

33:15.828 --> 33:18.956
<i>I'm serious!
You wanna go, now's the time.</i>

33:20.874 --> 33:22.876
Great!

33:23.002 --> 33:25.295
<i>Let's go.</i>

33:25.421 --> 33:28.382
Hey! Help up this surfer boy.

33:28.507 --> 33:31.719
He's one of the team now.
Let's go. Help him up!

33:33.178 --> 33:36.807
- The kid's OK. He's gonna be OK, David.
I need those pictures.

33:39.852 --> 33:43.188
David, I really need those pictures.

33:47.776 --> 33:50.279
(Knocking on door)

33:51.613 --> 33:52.906
<i>- Is this a bad time?</i>

33:53.032 --> 33:54.742
- Is there a problem?

33:54.867 --> 33:57.494
<i>- No, I just wanted to ask Mike</i>

33:57.619 --> 33:59.246
<i>if he had any special requests.</i>

33:59.371 --> 34:00.831
<i>- Yeah, I'll print them up.</i>

34:06.795 --> 34:07.880
<i>- He's moving too much.</i>

34:08.005 --> 34:10.674
<i>I can't get a decent frame.</i>

34:11.550 --> 34:14.719
- David, your head's moving too much.

34:14.844 --> 34:16.263
When you're on target,

34:16.388 --> 34:18.681
<i>try to hold still for a couple of seconds.</i>

34:21.601 --> 34:25.481
<i>- OK, David, I don't want to be a bugger, but go...</i>
- You OK?

34:27.608 --> 34:28.609
<i>- Sure.</i>

34:30.152 --> 34:33.362
<i>It's the pain. It's like
an electric shock sometimes.</i>

34:33.489 --> 34:36.949
<i>Give the Miatas to the new guys.
I want the high-paying stuff.</i>

34:37.076 --> 34:39.786
<i>- Just grab the paper and get to it!</i>

34:39.911 --> 34:43.456
<i>OK, David, just get me a shot
from behind the computer.</i>

34:43.581 --> 34:46.793
<i>No! What is he doing?
I don't wanna see that guy's face.</i>

34:46.918 --> 34:48.879
<i>- Is there a problem?
- Fuck that guy!</i>

34:49.004 --> 34:50.047
<i>- A big problem.</i>

34:50.172 --> 34:52.507
<i>- You can do it! Come on, David!</i>

34:52.632 --> 34:54.510
<i>Come on! Yes!</i>

34:54.635 --> 34:55.803
<i>Perfect, OK!</i>

34:55.928 --> 34:58.555
<i>That's the good stuff! Get closer! Closer!</i>

34:58.680 --> 35:00.015
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

35:00.432 --> 35:01.517
<i>- Yes! We got it!</i>

35:02.434 --> 35:04.019
<i>Tabarnak! It took you long, bud!</i>

35:04.144 --> 35:05.145
<i>- Michel...</i>

35:06.772 --> 35:10.317
<i>Do I need to make a spare key
every time I bring you a car?</i>

35:11.610 --> 35:13.779
<i>Thanks, Boss. Thanks, Michel.</i>

35:14.279 --> 35:16.573
(Martin): <i>We've got it. Good work, David.</i>

35:16.698 --> 35:20.828
<i>- Can you ask your overexcited poodle
to stop barking while I'm working?</i>

35:20.953 --> 35:22.663
(Chuckling): OK!

35:22.788 --> 35:24.581
- What the fuck, Mikey?
- I don't know.

35:24.706 --> 35:26.500
Maybe it's one of the mechanics.

35:26.625 --> 35:28.001
<i>- It's weird.
- What?</i>

35:28.127 --> 35:30.379
<i>- Mike gave me the same list as last week.</i>

35:30.796 --> 35:33.340
- Really? OK, you have to come in tonight.

35:33.465 --> 35:35.926
<i>- No way. I have to get at least one car tonight.</i>

35:36.051 --> 35:39.513
<i>Meet me in an hour at Ste-Catherine and Crescent.</i>
- 10-4.

35:39.638 --> 35:42.141
- Oh, and bring me a white shirt and a bow tie.

35:42.266 --> 35:45.269
<i>- What? A white shirt and a bow tie?</i>

35:45.394 --> 35:47.354
(♪ Bass thumping in distance ♪)

35:49.022 --> 35:52.276
<i>I can't believe you got me
helping you steal a car.</i>

35:53.527 --> 35:55.654
(♪ Pop on sound system ♪)

35:59.700 --> 36:01.034
<i>Whenever you're ready.</i>

36:01.160 --> 36:02.703
- On my way.

36:12.171 --> 36:13.881
<i>Merci.</i>

36:20.137 --> 36:21.096
<i>Good evening!</i>

36:21.638 --> 36:24.224
<i>Welcome to... 5!</i>

36:24.933 --> 36:26.435
<i>Have a good night!</i>

36:27.186 --> 36:30.772
(Woman): ♪♪ <i>No one makes me feel
like you do ♪</i>

36:30.898 --> 36:33.984
<i>♪ Love the way you light up the room ♪</i>

36:34.109 --> 36:37.821
<i>♪ No one makes me feel like you do... ♪</i>

36:39.031 --> 36:40.032
<i>Thanks.</i>

36:40.157 --> 36:43.076
<i>♪ Motorcycles with girls ♪</i>

36:43.202 --> 36:46.496
<i>♪ No one makes me feel like you do ♪</i>

36:46.622 --> 36:50.500
<i>♪ Love the way you light up the room ♪</i>

36:50.626 --> 36:54.963
<i>♪ No one makes me feel like you do ♪♪</i>

36:55.088 --> 36:58.300
Wow! That was too easy, man!

36:58.800 --> 37:00.302
<i>Let's do it again tomorrow!</i>

37:00.427 --> 37:01.720
- No way!

37:01.845 --> 37:06.183
I'm the one who has to pretend I lost my ticket,
then spend half an hour waiting for my car.

37:06.308 --> 37:08.268
(Laughing)

37:08.393 --> 37:10.520
(Man): ♪♪♪ <i>Princesse des ténèbres ♪</i>

37:10.646 --> 37:12.940
<i>♪ Archange maudit ♪</i>

37:15.067 --> 37:16.652
<i>♪ Amazone moderne style ♪</i>

37:16.777 --> 37:19.196
<i>♪ Que le sculpteur, en anglais ♪</i>

37:19.321 --> 37:23.075
<i>♪ Surnomma Spirit of Ecstasy... ♪♪</i>

37:36.004 --> 37:39.841
(Talking indistinctly)

37:49.726 --> 37:50.727
- Hey, Jen!

37:50.852 --> 37:53.355
<i>- What's up with that look?
Are you my barback tonight?</i>

37:53.480 --> 37:55.983
<i>- I have a little side gig going
with the symphony.</i>

37:56.108 --> 37:57.150
<i>You don't like it?</i>

37:58.068 --> 38:01.947
<i>I'll have a Jack and Coke.
- You sure you don't want a martini?</i>

38:04.241 --> 38:05.909
- Hi, Mike.

38:24.469 --> 38:26.221
Martin?

38:26.346 --> 38:27.848
<i>Martin, can you hear me?</i>

38:27.973 --> 38:28.849
<i>Wake up!</i>

38:28.974 --> 38:31.184
- I'm here! I'm here!
Is something wrong?

38:31.310 --> 38:34.521
<i>- The three clients are at the bar.</i>
You need to tell them...

38:34.646 --> 38:35.897
<i>It's too risky for me.</i>

38:36.023 --> 38:37.149
<i>- I'll be there in 10.</i>

38:37.274 --> 38:38.775
<i>- Do it quick!</i>

38:48.660 --> 38:51.038
<i>That's right, I talk to my penis.</i>

38:51.163 --> 38:52.456
(Martin chuckling)

38:52.581 --> 38:57.169
<i>I've even given him a name: Martin.
- Ha! Asshole!</i>

38:57.294 --> 39:00.881
<i>- I don't give a damn!
Do what you want.</i>

39:01.465 --> 39:05.344
<i>Just don't ask me to introduce you to mine.</i>
- OK.

39:06.261 --> 39:08.680
<i>I'll be at the bar if you change your mind.</i>

39:11.183 --> 39:13.393
<i>- Mike wants me to take care of them.</i>

39:14.311 --> 39:16.688
<i>- Who are they?
- I don't know.</i>

39:16.813 --> 39:18.065
<i>I don't ask questions,</i>

39:18.190 --> 39:20.817
<i>as long as they tip well
and take it easy on the groping.</i>

39:21.443 --> 39:26.239
<i>- Gina? Jen? Can I have another?
This one's empty.</i>

39:26.365 --> 39:29.451
<i>A double. And three more
for my friends over there.</i>

39:29.576 --> 39:30.702
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

39:30.827 --> 39:33.080
<i>- Five minutes, tops!</i>

39:36.416 --> 39:38.085
<i>- Jen, do you have any matches?</i>

39:44.674 --> 39:46.301
<i>- Uh-oh! They're angry!</i>

39:46.426 --> 39:48.136
<i>Don't worry, it's just liquid!</i>

39:48.261 --> 39:50.639
<i>Dry it off with your turban!</i>
- Yo, what's he saying?

39:50.764 --> 39:53.141
<i>- Get the hell out!
- I'll take care of it.</i>

39:53.266 --> 39:54.226
(Groaning)

39:54.351 --> 39:57.437
<i>Come on!
- What are you doing, man?</i>

39:57.562 --> 39:59.648
- It's all right.
- What's his problem?

39:59.773 --> 40:00.774
- That's nothing.

40:07.280 --> 40:08.949
<i>- Salut!</i>

40:09.074 --> 40:10.325
- OK!

40:11.910 --> 40:14.996
<i>Go home and come back tomorrow.</i>

40:15.122 --> 40:16.289
- OK!
- OK?

40:16.415 --> 40:18.792
<i>- That way? Tomorrow?
- Good night!</i>

40:22.421 --> 40:24.464
- I'm here.

40:25.841 --> 40:28.552
<i>- Listen, big shot!
- Is he still here?</i>

40:28.969 --> 40:33.014
<i>- You guys can't tell me what to do
in my own--</i>

40:33.140 --> 40:34.474
(Grunting)

41:12.804 --> 41:13.930
<i>- Do you have a light?</i>

41:22.814 --> 41:25.066
(Muttering indistinctly)

41:45.504 --> 41:46.963
(Coughing)

41:57.349 --> 41:58.808
<i>I'm going inside.</i>

42:09.361 --> 42:13.240
- David, you won't fucking believe this!

42:17.827 --> 42:19.454
<i>- You sure about that?</i>

42:19.579 --> 42:20.956
- No, Dave, I'm not 100% sure,

42:21.081 --> 42:24.167
but seeing as there were
3 American flags hanging off the building,

42:24.292 --> 42:27.420
2 armed Marines at the door,
oh, and yes, a gold plaque that says:

42:27.546 --> 42:29.631
"United States of America Consulate,"

42:29.756 --> 42:31.591
I think I might be onto something.

42:31.967 --> 42:34.427
<i>- What are they doing there?
- They're American.</i>

42:35.262 --> 42:37.389
<i>- Yeah, and I'm Japanese.</i>

42:37.514 --> 42:41.518
<i>On Saturdays, I put on my flip-flops
and make sushi at the mall.</i>

42:41.643 --> 42:43.436
- She's right. They are Americans.

42:43.562 --> 42:44.813
Show him.

42:50.443 --> 42:52.487
<i>- They're all at the same university.</i>

42:52.988 --> 42:55.240
<i>- What system did you hack into?
- None.</i>

42:55.365 --> 42:57.033
<i>They're all properly enrolled.</i>

42:57.158 --> 42:59.327
<i>They're even listed in our official database</i>

42:59.452 --> 43:01.997
<i>as humanitarian observers and consultants.</i>

43:02.581 --> 43:05.959
<i>- For who? Crooks Without Borders?
- That's not a real thing.</i>

43:07.627 --> 43:09.004
<i>- Thanks, Princess Leia.</i>

43:10.755 --> 43:12.549
- What if they're FBI?

43:12.674 --> 43:14.134
<i>- Fuck, this is heavy!</i>

43:14.259 --> 43:15.969
- They're rocks!

43:17.053 --> 43:18.263
- FBI?

43:18.388 --> 43:19.889
- Mm-hmm!

43:20.015 --> 43:22.183
- Nah! No, no, no.

43:22.309 --> 43:23.685
<i>What next?</i>

43:23.810 --> 43:28.356
<i>Are the KGB and Scotland Yard on their way
for middle management like DiPietro?</i>

43:29.190 --> 43:33.403
- OK, you take care of DiPietro,
and I'll keep my eyes on the Americans.

43:33.820 --> 43:36.698
<i>- Great. Keep me posted.</i>
- Hey!

43:36.823 --> 43:38.992
Aren't you forgetting something?

43:39.117 --> 43:40.201
- Uh, no.

43:40.327 --> 43:41.828
- Uh, the tip?

43:41.953 --> 43:43.330
<i>- What tip?</i>

43:43.455 --> 43:47.083
- Yesterday, the guy whose car you stole,
he gave you a tip.

43:47.208 --> 43:48.376
$20, right?

43:49.044 --> 43:50.045
<i>- Yeah, and?</i>

43:50.170 --> 43:54.090
- Well, I tipped the valet, too,
and I'd like to get my money back.

43:55.216 --> 43:56.801
- Man!

43:56.926 --> 43:59.137
You're so cheap!

43:59.262 --> 44:01.556
(Both chuckling)

44:03.183 --> 44:05.352
<i>How much did you tip him?</i>
- $10 bucks!

44:08.146 --> 44:09.773
<i>- I want my change.</i>

44:09.898 --> 44:12.400
- And you're calling me cheap.

44:18.156 --> 44:20.909
<i>- You're $5 short.
- No!</i>

44:22.160 --> 44:24.245
I paid $10, you got $20,

44:24.371 --> 44:27.207
the profit is $10, so your share is $5.

44:29.417 --> 44:31.294
<i>- Tabarnak!</i>

44:31.419 --> 44:35.215
You need help. You need therapy, my friend.

44:35.340 --> 44:36.424
Hey!

44:36.549 --> 44:40.303
<i>You should be in AA. Or maybe in CC...</i>
"Cheap Canadians."

44:40.428 --> 44:44.015
"Hi, my name is Martin!"
"Hi, Martin!"

44:44.140 --> 44:46.351
"I've been a cheap Canadian since I was born,

44:46.476 --> 44:50.105
"and I'm so excited to get 5 bucks,
I'm still shaking."

44:55.068 --> 44:59.280
<i>- Here! Swap this out!</i>
- Whoa! <i>You seem to think I work for you.</i>

44:59.406 --> 45:01.116
- Ah!

45:01.241 --> 45:03.910
<i>I'm sorry. Didn't I explain this to you?</i>

45:04.994 --> 45:06.538
<i>Federal...</i>

45:11.042 --> 45:11.960
<i>provincial.</i>

45:12.794 --> 45:16.965
<i>- That's not the best way to talk
to a separatist with anger issues!</i>

45:17.090 --> 45:19.175
<i>- Watch your mouth, young man!</i>

45:19.300 --> 45:22.971
<i>This morning, my endocrinologist
told me I wasn't the right sex!</i>

45:23.096 --> 45:25.557
<i>My testosterone level is abnormally high:</i>

45:25.682 --> 45:28.226
<i>women are at 2, men are at 7,</i>

45:28.351 --> 45:30.228
<i>and I'm a fucking 9.2!</i>

45:36.818 --> 45:38.778
(Door slamming)

45:41.531 --> 45:44.409
<i>- At least she's seeing a professional.</i>

45:47.245 --> 45:48.997
(Car honking)

45:54.377 --> 45:57.964
- Martin Ward, RCMP.
I need to see an official.

45:58.089 --> 46:02.093
It's regarding
a very important and delicate matter.

46:02.218 --> 46:04.512
- Everything is important, sir.

46:04.637 --> 46:07.056
Take a blue number.
Take a seat right there.

46:07.182 --> 46:09.267
Somebody will be with you shortly.

46:12.520 --> 46:13.813
<i>- Have a nice day!</i>

46:14.939 --> 46:16.941
<i>Hello! Can I take your order?</i>

46:17.066 --> 46:19.235
<i>- Yes, I'd like the surf and turf,</i>

46:19.360 --> 46:21.738
<i>a baked potato with foie gras</i>

46:21.863 --> 46:23.948
<i>and a glass of red wine, please.</i>

46:24.073 --> 46:26.743
<i>- Dad! OK, anything else?</i>

46:28.912 --> 46:30.872
<i>- I needed to see your face.</i>

46:32.791 --> 46:35.752
<i>Are you ready for your exam?
- Yes, I'm ready.</i>

46:35.877 --> 46:37.587
<i>Nervous, but ready.</i>

46:37.712 --> 46:40.924
<i>- Let's go over the steps involved
in a civilian intervention.</i>

46:41.049 --> 46:43.218
<i>- Dad, I'm ready!
- Tut, tut, tut!</i>

46:43.343 --> 46:44.427
<i>Envoie!</i>

46:45.887 --> 46:48.723
<i>- Approach, identification, questioning, listening,</i>

46:48.848 --> 46:51.100
<i>situation analysis, conflict resolution.</i>

46:51.226 --> 46:53.353
<i>- And if you can't resolve the conflict?</i>

46:53.478 --> 46:56.105
<i>- I'll do what you'd do:
make up a law or pull my gun.</i>

46:56.231 --> 46:57.482
<i>- Ha ha ha!</i>

46:57.607 --> 46:59.526
<i>Very funny!</i>

46:59.651 --> 47:01.402
(Laughing)
<i>- I'm ready, Dad.</i>

47:01.528 --> 47:04.614
<i>- I know you are. If I passed it,
then you'll ace it.</i>

47:05.865 --> 47:07.033
<i>- Thanks.</i>

47:07.158 --> 47:09.786
(Car honking)
- Hey!

47:10.161 --> 47:12.997
<i>Let's go, moron!
- Calm down!</i>

47:13.122 --> 47:16.459
<i>There are 40 different donuts!
I need a minute to choose!</i>

47:16.584 --> 47:18.169
<i>- Dad!
- I don't have all day!</i>

47:18.294 --> 47:20.088
(Speaking gibberish)

47:20.213 --> 47:22.549
<i>- Drive up to the first window, please.</i>

47:22.674 --> 47:24.759
(♪ Muzak on PA ♪)

47:33.935 --> 47:35.895
(Groaning quietly)

47:38.898 --> 47:40.358
(Machine whirring)

48:07.594 --> 48:09.512
(Sighing)

48:09.637 --> 48:11.139
<i>$4. 75.</i>

48:14.267 --> 48:17.812
<i>- Can you do me a favour?
Buy some ice cream for your mother.</i>

48:17.937 --> 48:20.106
<i>Honey-lavender.
- Gross.</i>

48:20.440 --> 48:24.444
<i>- I can't believe that even exists.
They need a bacon and ribs flavour.</i>

48:24.569 --> 48:26.112
(Gabrielle laughing)

48:27.071 --> 48:28.615
OK?

48:28.740 --> 48:30.700
- OK.

48:31.743 --> 48:32.869
<i>Here.</i>

48:39.918 --> 48:40.793
<i>- Smile!</i>

48:49.385 --> 48:51.971
- Babe, 2 sandwiches for the price of one!

48:52.096 --> 48:53.681
(Both laughing)

48:56.601 --> 48:57.894
- What?

49:04.525 --> 49:06.527
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

49:09.656 --> 49:12.492
- We're serving number 159, sir.

49:12.617 --> 49:14.452
- Perhaps you've made a mistake

49:14.577 --> 49:17.163
and slipped by a couple too quickly?

49:17.288 --> 49:19.415
- Impossible. It's all done by computer.

49:19.540 --> 49:21.501
The numbers are not switched manually.

49:21.626 --> 49:24.712
- I need to speak to somebody now!

49:24.837 --> 49:25.838
- Ken!

49:30.885 --> 49:32.178
We have a Code 63.

49:32.303 --> 49:34.555
- Code 63? What the heck is that?

49:34.681 --> 49:37.266
- Please... Thanks, Clo. Take your 15.

49:37.392 --> 49:39.310
I got this.

49:39.435 --> 49:41.521
(Sighing)

49:41.646 --> 49:45.566
- Look, I'm sorry--
- The paper we gave you on your way in.

49:48.319 --> 49:51.406
- The reason for my impatience...

49:51.531 --> 49:53.324
In fact, the entire visit here--

49:57.120 --> 49:59.080
(Keyboard clicking)

50:01.833 --> 50:03.876
- I'm sorry, sir. No one can see you today.

50:04.002 --> 50:07.839
But if you want to come back tomorrow,
I'm sure I can get you on another list.

50:07.964 --> 50:08.923
- Fuck you!

50:12.719 --> 50:15.138
<i>- You're beautiful.
- You too.</i>

50:16.222 --> 50:18.349
<i>But I don't miss your biker look.</i>

50:18.474 --> 50:21.936
<i>- I don't believe you! You love bad boys!</i>

50:22.061 --> 50:23.646
<i>(Chuckling)</i>

50:25.398 --> 50:26.774
<i>- How'd you do that?</i>

50:27.316 --> 50:29.736
<i>- I have an in with your tenant.</i>

50:31.070 --> 50:34.115
<i>- I knew I was right to remarry you!</i>

50:34.240 --> 50:35.491
<i>You're the perfect man:</i>

50:35.616 --> 50:39.912
<i>you're never here, so you feel bad
and do cute things like this!</i>

50:40.872 --> 50:42.290
<i>Hang on.</i>

50:46.294 --> 50:47.795
<i>You OK?</i>

50:48.671 --> 50:51.799
<i>- No. This is tough.</i>

50:52.550 --> 50:54.260
<i>- I know, my love.</i>

50:54.385 --> 50:57.722
<i>But it's almost over.
- It's never over.</i>

51:00.183 --> 51:02.185
<i>Sometimes I wonder why I do all this,</i>

51:02.310 --> 51:04.145
<i>just to catch a couple crooks.</i>

51:04.937 --> 51:06.856
<i>Then the trial will take years,</i>

51:06.981 --> 51:10.276
<i>and if any evidence gets thrown out,
the whole thing goes down the drain!</i>

51:10.401 --> 51:12.320
<i>- Can you put my husband on?</i>

51:12.445 --> 51:14.822
<i>My man never talks this way.</i>

51:14.947 --> 51:18.659
<i>Do you know him?
- No. What's he like?</i>

51:18.785 --> 51:21.954
<i>- He's a stubborn bastard with a bad temper,</i>

51:22.080 --> 51:26.959
<i>but he's the bravest, most honest,
most determined man there is.</i>

51:28.586 --> 51:29.921
<i>- Go on.</i>

51:30.046 --> 51:32.006
<i>- He's an alpha male.</i>

51:32.131 --> 51:34.133
