01:09:05.850 --> 01:09:09.437
(Anglophone accent):
The Sûreté du Québec.

01:09:09.563 --> 01:09:11.773
- He's totally making that up.

01:09:11.898 --> 01:09:12.774
- Mm-hmm.

01:09:12.899 --> 01:09:15.193
- Are you a German?

01:09:15.318 --> 01:09:16.611
- What?

01:09:18.988 --> 01:09:21.700
No. No! I'm French.

01:09:21.825 --> 01:09:23.410
- French?

01:09:24.786 --> 01:09:27.913
Well, now, I thought you said you was Canadian!

01:09:28.038 --> 01:09:30.667
- Oh!
- He's got him!

01:09:30.792 --> 01:09:32.961
- Really?
- Sure.

01:09:33.086 --> 01:09:36.298
First he says he's French, and then Canadian?

01:09:36.423 --> 01:09:40.051
- Uh, pretty sure there are French Canadians.

01:09:40.176 --> 01:09:41.261
(Both men chuckling)

01:09:41.386 --> 01:09:43.555
- French... French Can...?

01:09:43.680 --> 01:09:46.600
- Which is it, son? You French or Canadian?

01:09:46.725 --> 01:09:48.225
- I'm Quebecois, <i>calice!</i>

01:09:48.350 --> 01:09:51.563
French-Canadian, <i>séparatiste libérale, tabernak!</i>

01:09:51.688 --> 01:09:52.814
<i>Where are you from?</i>

01:09:52.939 --> 01:09:55.317
<i>United Stupids of America?
Or South Moronia?</i>

01:09:55.442 --> 01:09:56.443
<i>You fucking dumbass!</i>

01:09:56.568 --> 01:09:57.944
- OK, that was not French.

01:09:58.069 --> 01:10:00.238
- Yeah, it sounded more like Swedish.

01:10:00.363 --> 01:10:04.201
- Yeah! Like the Swedish Chef on <i>The Muppets.</i>

01:10:05.285 --> 01:10:07.204
- Hmm?

01:10:07.329 --> 01:10:08.413
- The...

01:10:08.538 --> 01:10:10.707
(Speaking Swedish-sounding gibberish)

01:10:10.832 --> 01:10:11.750
- Ah.

01:10:11.875 --> 01:10:13.210
- No, that was French.

01:10:13.335 --> 01:10:16.171
Like, it might be some kind of, like, street,

01:10:16.296 --> 01:10:19.090
weird, 2nd-rate, bastardized kind of French,

01:10:19.216 --> 01:10:20.508
but that was French.

01:10:20.634 --> 01:10:23.511
- I'm pretty sure it was Swedish.
- Mm.

01:10:23.637 --> 01:10:26.723
- You best get your story straight there, son!

01:10:26.848 --> 01:10:29.267
The FBI is on the way.

01:10:29.392 --> 01:10:31.228
- The FBI?
- Mm-hmm.

01:10:31.853 --> 01:10:34.606
And they won't be nearly as kind as we are!

01:10:37.317 --> 01:10:39.110
- Whew! FBI's coming here?

01:10:39.236 --> 01:10:40.654
- Mm.

01:10:42.280 --> 01:10:45.867
- Hallelujah! Praise the Lord!

01:10:46.576 --> 01:10:48.161
I'll wait for them, then.

01:10:48.286 --> 01:10:50.330
Thanks for your participation.

01:10:50.455 --> 01:10:51.623
Very appreciated.

01:10:54.668 --> 01:10:56.962
- Uh, you sure about that?

01:10:57.087 --> 01:10:59.005
<i>- Yep! Damn sure!</i>

01:10:59.130 --> 01:11:01.675
(Speaking Swedish-sounding gibberish)

01:11:01.800 --> 01:11:05.262
- You're sure?
Because if you... wanted to straighten anything up...

01:11:06.471 --> 01:11:09.724
more than happy to have a little chinwag...
(Chuckling)

01:11:09.849 --> 01:11:11.559
<i>...mano a mano.</i>

01:11:17.357 --> 01:11:20.610
(♪ Whistling <i>Auld Lang Syne</i> ♪)

01:11:30.287 --> 01:11:32.414
Well!
(Clearing throat)

01:11:32.539 --> 01:11:34.416
Can't say I didn't warn you!

01:11:45.635 --> 01:11:46.678
Well...

01:11:48.179 --> 01:11:50.932
I guess I stirred his giblets pretty good.

01:12:00.150 --> 01:12:01.359
(Sighing)

01:12:04.988 --> 01:12:06.865
(Sirens wailing)

01:12:12.203 --> 01:12:14.622
- All right. Let's make sure that bridge is safe.

01:12:14.748 --> 01:12:17.459
Let's take all the time that we need
to process this crime scene properly.

01:12:17.584 --> 01:12:19.544
I want Command and Central
up and running in ten.

01:12:19.669 --> 01:12:23.214
And get the mayor on the line
and tell him to meet me here in half an hour.

01:12:23.340 --> 01:12:26.718
- Yes, sir, excuse me, can I get...
- Sir, sir, sir! Just a few...

01:12:28.511 --> 01:12:30.889
- I'm gonna make a brief statement.

01:12:31.014 --> 01:12:34.225
- Sir, do we have information
on who committed this act of extreme violence?

01:12:34.351 --> 01:12:36.644
- Do you think that this attack
was terrorist-related?

01:12:36.770 --> 01:12:40.065
- The statement does not include questions.
However, I can say that this act

01:12:40.190 --> 01:12:43.109
was in no way related
to a terrorist organization.

01:12:43.234 --> 01:12:44.694
We do have a suspect in custody,

01:12:44.819 --> 01:12:47.447
and I will keep you posted
on any future developments.

01:12:47.572 --> 01:12:50.283
- Can you give us the name of the suspect?

01:12:50.408 --> 01:12:52.744
- I want the good people
of Middlebrook to know

01:12:52.869 --> 01:12:54.496
that they are safe tonight.

01:12:54.621 --> 01:12:56.998
Rest assured, there are no further threats.

01:12:57.123 --> 01:12:58.917
- Martin Ward, RCMP.
- Stay back.

01:12:59.042 --> 01:13:01.753
- I need to speak to whoever's in charge.

01:13:05.215 --> 01:13:06.800
- Agent Blaine, FBI.

01:13:06.925 --> 01:13:10.804
- I have information that'll be of great use to you.
- Oh, really?

01:13:17.394 --> 01:13:20.688
- David. Agent Blaine, FBI.

01:13:23.942 --> 01:13:27.487
- Is this man here your partner?
- Well, partner is a relative term.

01:13:27.612 --> 01:13:29.239
- Martin!
- Yes, he is.

01:13:29.364 --> 01:13:31.866
This is David Bouchard
from the Sûreté du Québec.

01:13:31.991 --> 01:13:33.201
He is one of my men.

01:13:33.326 --> 01:13:35.995
- Then, sir, I'm gonna
have to ask you to turn around

01:13:36.121 --> 01:13:38.373
and slowly put your hands on the table.

01:13:38.498 --> 01:13:39.958
- What?

01:13:40.083 --> 01:13:40.917
- Mm.

01:13:41.042 --> 01:13:42.168
- I'm RCMP!

01:13:42.293 --> 01:13:44.921
- Sir! I'm not gonna ask again.

01:13:57.183 --> 01:14:00.186
<i>- Did you really think they'd let me go</i>

01:14:00.311 --> 01:14:03.314
<i>because you flashed
your little Canadian police badge?</i>

01:14:03.982 --> 01:14:05.483
<i>You're so naïve!</i>

01:14:06.025 --> 01:14:09.154
<i>You haven't become
a Jehovah's Witness, have you?</i>

01:14:09.988 --> 01:14:12.490
<i>I was driving a car that exploded</i>

01:14:12.615 --> 01:14:15.827
<i>in the country with the most
terrorist threats in the world!</i>

01:14:15.952 --> 01:14:18.955
<i>Now, instead of just me
being stuck here, we both are!</i>

01:14:19.080 --> 01:14:20.915
<i>Good job!</i>

01:14:23.543 --> 01:14:26.713
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
my partner, Martin Ward!</i>

01:14:27.547 --> 01:14:28.756
RCMP!

01:14:28.882 --> 01:14:30.341
(Sighing)

01:14:38.266 --> 01:14:39.726
I'm sorry.

01:14:40.768 --> 01:14:42.270
- What for?

01:14:43.605 --> 01:14:46.191
<i>- You know. Don't rub it in.</i>

01:14:46.316 --> 01:14:49.360
- But there are just so many to choose from!

01:14:54.115 --> 01:14:55.575
- Fuck you.

01:14:55.700 --> 01:14:57.744
(Both chuckling)

01:14:58.703 --> 01:15:01.623
- Do you think the other 25 cars
are rigged like yours?

01:15:01.748 --> 01:15:03.249
<i>- Definitely!</i>

01:15:04.250 --> 01:15:07.712
<i>It's brilliant: you disseminate
stolen cars all over the States</i>

01:15:07.837 --> 01:15:09.589
<i>and simultaneously blow them up!</i>

01:15:09.714 --> 01:15:12.717
- Even if somebody knows that something's wrong,
who's gonna say anything?

01:15:12.842 --> 01:15:14.594
I mean, they bought a stolen car.

01:15:14.969 --> 01:15:16.888
<i>- What do we do if we get out?</i>

01:15:17.013 --> 01:15:20.350
- I'll get my team together.
We'll go back in, get those computers out.

01:15:20.975 --> 01:15:24.020
We need the FBI to believe us, or we're done.

01:15:33.029 --> 01:15:34.447
- Shaking again?

01:15:38.159 --> 01:15:42.539
<i>Is it that hard for you
to be alone in a room with me?</i>

01:15:43.081 --> 01:15:44.582
- You wish!

01:15:47.627 --> 01:15:48.920
<i>- What is it?</i>

01:15:51.005 --> 01:15:52.924
- I'm cold.

01:15:56.636 --> 01:15:58.137
<i>- What is it?</i>

01:15:58.721 --> 01:16:01.599
<i>This isn't the first time. What's going on?</i>

01:16:10.316 --> 01:16:11.818
(Sighing)

01:16:12.694 --> 01:16:14.195
<i>- I'm sick, David.</i>

01:16:15.321 --> 01:16:16.531
Very.

01:16:18.533 --> 01:16:19.951
- What is it?

01:16:23.079 --> 01:16:25.206
<i>- I have Lou Gehrig's disease.</i>

01:16:29.043 --> 01:16:30.503
- OK.

01:16:31.546 --> 01:16:33.298
<i>Who's Lou Gehrig?</i>

01:16:33.423 --> 01:16:37.635
<i>- He was a baseball player.
Had one of the first known cases.</i>

01:16:42.390 --> 01:16:43.891
<i>- I don't know baseball.</i>

01:16:45.393 --> 01:16:47.186
<i>Is it like Parkinson's?</i>

01:16:47.770 --> 01:16:49.314
- Well...

01:16:49.439 --> 01:16:51.774
<i>It's a degenerative disease.</i>

01:16:52.400 --> 01:16:56.613
I'm slowly losing control
of my motor functions.

01:16:56.738 --> 01:17:01.659
So... one by one,
things will shut down.

01:17:01.784 --> 01:17:03.244
And the fun part is,

01:17:03.369 --> 01:17:06.539
you never know what, when or in what order.

01:17:06.664 --> 01:17:10.585
Just that they're all gonna go. Eventually.

01:17:11.586 --> 01:17:14.881
<i>It's like Russian roulette.</i>

01:17:15.423 --> 01:17:18.593
Hey, Martin.
What are you gonna lose today?

01:17:18.718 --> 01:17:20.386
The ability to swallow...

01:17:22.472 --> 01:17:23.931
or speak?

01:17:28.019 --> 01:17:29.729
<i>- That could take years.</i>

01:17:29.854 --> 01:17:32.148
- Not many. Six, maybe seven.

01:17:32.273 --> 01:17:36.986
And the last few aren't that much fun, so I hear.

01:17:37.111 --> 01:17:38.071
(Sighing)

01:17:40.698 --> 01:17:42.742
<i>- There must be medication.</i>

01:17:42.867 --> 01:17:46.704
- Yeah. I'm taking them.
They slow it down, but...

01:17:55.380 --> 01:17:56.881
- I'm sorry, man.

01:17:58.174 --> 01:18:00.009
(Breathing deeply)

01:18:06.891 --> 01:18:08.351
<i>calice!</i>

01:18:16.484 --> 01:18:20.947
And you thought being stuck with me
was the worst thing that could happen to you?

01:18:21.072 --> 01:18:22.990
- Oh, it still is.

01:18:23.116 --> 01:18:25.243
(Both chuckling)

01:18:26.828 --> 01:18:28.287
I want...

01:18:32.625 --> 01:18:36.087
I need to win this one.

01:18:40.633 --> 01:18:42.427
I don't wanna step down...

01:18:43.928 --> 01:18:45.972
just a sick, old man.

01:18:47.390 --> 01:18:48.558
You know?

01:18:50.351 --> 01:18:51.519
- You won't.

01:19:01.654 --> 01:19:03.156
You won't.

01:19:16.335 --> 01:19:18.296
(Birds chirping)

01:19:27.472 --> 01:19:29.348
- Gentlemen!

01:19:29.474 --> 01:19:30.850
You're good to go.

01:19:30.975 --> 01:19:33.644
- Huh?
- Everything checked out.

01:19:35.062 --> 01:19:38.858
- There are about 25 more cars, we think,
rigged just like this one.

01:19:38.983 --> 01:19:42.320
- We don't know when the shit's gonna go down,
but we think it's gonna be pretty soon.

01:19:42.445 --> 01:19:44.322
- So what's our next move?
- I don't know.

01:19:44.447 --> 01:19:47.492
- You don't know what your next move is?
- Oh, <i>my</i> next move?

01:19:47.617 --> 01:19:49.744
My next move is to escort you to the border,

01:19:49.869 --> 01:19:52.622
shake your hands,
thank you kindly and wish you luck.

01:19:52.747 --> 01:19:56.334
And your next move
will be to file all the necessary paperwork

01:19:56.459 --> 01:19:59.504
that we're gonna need
to conclude this investigation.

01:19:59.629 --> 01:20:02.465
But your superiors
are gonna explain all of that to you,

01:20:02.590 --> 01:20:05.259
in both official languages, when you return.

01:20:05.384 --> 01:20:08.387
Oh, and gents, next time you feel like

01:20:08.513 --> 01:20:12.183
crashing into my backyard
and stirring up a shitstorm,

01:20:12.308 --> 01:20:14.185
do me a favour: call me first

01:20:14.310 --> 01:20:17.855
so I can tell you to stay
the fuck away from my country!

01:20:19.941 --> 01:20:21.442
<i>- What an asshole!</i>

01:20:23.569 --> 01:20:26.197
- He kind of reminds me of you when we met.

01:20:47.885 --> 01:20:49.720
- Where is everybody?

01:20:50.221 --> 01:20:54.559
<i>- The big boss pulled the plug, Boss.</i>
- Why are you still here, then?

01:20:54.684 --> 01:20:57.645
<i>- My boss is you, Boss. Not your boss.</i>
- What?

01:20:57.770 --> 01:20:59.021
<i>- Don't ask me.</i>

01:20:59.146 --> 01:21:01.899
<i>- There's no signal. I don't understand.</i>

01:21:02.024 --> 01:21:03.568
<i>What the fuck?</i>

01:21:03.693 --> 01:21:06.279
<i>- Are they still in the garage?
- No.</i>

01:21:06.404 --> 01:21:08.698
- Don't you have a tracker
on the device you had David switch?

01:21:08.823 --> 01:21:09.991
<i>- Yes, but there's no signal.</i>

01:21:10.116 --> 01:21:11.951
<i>- OK. The consulate.</i>

01:21:12.076 --> 01:21:15.872
- We can't touch them. They're on American soil.
Besides, we don't even know if they're still there.

01:21:17.373 --> 01:21:21.961
- Fucking fuck the fuck the fucking fuck!

01:21:23.379 --> 01:21:26.007
- Always one move behind.

01:21:30.303 --> 01:21:31.512
- OK.

01:21:38.686 --> 01:21:39.770
Jen!

01:21:39.896 --> 01:21:41.731
- Are you sure he's here?

01:21:41.856 --> 01:21:45.109
<i>- Yes, the bartender kept me in touch.
There is hardly anyone left.</i>

01:21:55.369 --> 01:21:58.331
<i>- We're closed! Don't you have a watch?</i>
- Oh! I'm sorry!

01:21:58.456 --> 01:22:00.333
My watch is still on Vancouver time,

01:22:00.458 --> 01:22:02.960
which means we've still got several hours left.

01:22:03.085 --> 01:22:05.129
So step right back inside.

01:22:05.254 --> 01:22:06.756
<i>- Salut!</i>

01:22:07.465 --> 01:22:08.716
<i>Remember me?</i>

01:22:12.178 --> 01:22:15.890
<i>I don't know this Lou Gehrig,
but he must've been a hell of a player!</i>

01:22:16.307 --> 01:22:18.392
<i>Sorry, too soon?</i>

01:22:20.478 --> 01:22:22.396
(Screaming)

01:22:23.856 --> 01:22:24.857
<i>- Fuck!</i>

01:22:25.441 --> 01:22:28.152
- Police! Everybody out!
We're looking for a Mike.

01:22:28.277 --> 01:22:29.904
(Groaning)

01:22:33.032 --> 01:22:34.992
<i>- OK, everybody out!</i> Mike!

01:22:37.119 --> 01:22:38.412
<i>Michel!</i>

01:22:40.206 --> 01:22:41.207
<i>Mikey!</i>

01:22:42.625 --> 01:22:45.086
<i>I know you're here, Mikey!</i>
(Jen whimpering)

01:22:45.211 --> 01:22:46.671
<i>- OK, easy! Easy there!</i>

01:22:48.839 --> 01:22:50.132
- Mike!

01:22:52.343 --> 01:22:56.681
<i>Don't make me shoot. Let her go.
She didn't know I was a cop!</i>

01:22:56.806 --> 01:22:58.391
- There's no way out.
The place is surrounded.

01:22:58.516 --> 01:23:02.520
<i>- Shut up! I'm getting out of here,
or I slit her throat. Got it?</i>

01:23:02.645 --> 01:23:03.854
- Mike!

01:23:03.980 --> 01:23:08.359
<i>Let her go, and we'll put
our guns down so we can talk.</i>

01:23:08.484 --> 01:23:11.278
<i>- What kind of idiot do you think I am?</i>
(Cops): Mike!

01:23:11.404 --> 01:23:12.613
<i>- Don't move!</i>

01:23:12.738 --> 01:23:15.074
- Nobody's died yet.
You can still get out of this.

01:23:15.199 --> 01:23:18.452
<i>- Shut up! I'll bleed her dry, goddammit!</i>

01:23:18.577 --> 01:23:20.496
- Mike! Mike! Mike! Mike! Mike!

01:23:20.621 --> 01:23:21.914
<i>Calm down! Look!</i>

01:23:23.541 --> 01:23:25.459
<i>I'm putting down my gun.</i>

01:23:25.584 --> 01:23:26.877
- David! Don't!

01:23:27.003 --> 01:23:28.546
<i>- Let him go. He'll kill her.</i>

01:23:28.671 --> 01:23:29.964
- No! No!

01:23:30.089 --> 01:23:32.299
<i>- Put your gun down!
- Drop it!</i>

01:23:32.425 --> 01:23:34.218
- Martin!
<i>- Tell him to drop it!</i>

01:23:34.343 --> 01:23:35.302
- No!

01:23:36.345 --> 01:23:38.472
You listen to me.

01:23:38.597 --> 01:23:41.600
If you hurt that girl, I will shoot you,

01:23:41.726 --> 01:23:44.020
you intolerable piece of shit!

01:23:44.729 --> 01:23:46.522
(Yelping)

01:23:46.647 --> 01:23:49.984
(Screaming)

01:23:50.109 --> 01:23:51.777
(Roaring)

01:23:58.034 --> 01:23:59.910
<i>- You fucking psychopath!</i>

01:24:03.914 --> 01:24:06.417
<i>Abusive motherfucking pimp!</i>

01:24:11.380 --> 01:24:14.258
<i>You won't be grabbing anyone's ass anymore!</i>

01:24:18.137 --> 01:24:19.722
- OK, OK, OK!

01:24:20.931 --> 01:24:22.308
(Panting)

01:24:24.477 --> 01:24:26.854
<i>OK, two more?
What do you think, Martin?</i>

01:24:26.979 --> 01:24:30.066
- Yeah, two's right.
But not too hard, we need to talk to him.

01:24:30.983 --> 01:24:32.651
(Grunting)

01:24:33.778 --> 01:24:36.113
<i>- OK, it's over.</i>

01:24:48.000 --> 01:24:49.752
- We have to go.

01:24:49.877 --> 01:24:51.378
- That fucking bitch!

01:24:54.757 --> 01:24:56.258
<i>- Are you all right?</i>

01:24:57.593 --> 01:24:59.011
- Mm-hmm.

01:24:59.136 --> 01:25:01.305
<i>- As soon as we're gone, call 911.</i>

01:25:02.890 --> 01:25:07.269
<i>- Aren't you the police?
- Yes, but no.</i>

01:25:08.020 --> 01:25:12.108
<i>You understand?
- No, but yes.</i>

01:25:12.525 --> 01:25:15.027
<i>- As soon as we leave, call 911.</i>

01:25:15.152 --> 01:25:18.072
<i>Tell them someone's been seriously injured.
Then get out.</i>

01:25:18.197 --> 01:25:20.699
<i>Make sure you're gone before they get here.</i>

01:25:20.825 --> 01:25:22.159
<i>You have a boyfriend?</i>

01:25:22.535 --> 01:25:26.247
<i>Good. Go to his place
and stay there until I call you.</i>

01:25:26.372 --> 01:25:30.334
<i>I'll call you when this is all over.
Then you can teach me some of those moves.</i>

01:25:31.877 --> 01:25:33.129
OK?

01:25:34.797 --> 01:25:36.298
<i>Thanks, Jen.</i>

01:25:43.305 --> 01:25:44.515
(Mike grunting)

01:25:44.640 --> 01:25:46.058
<i>- You can't do this, motherfuckers!</i>

01:25:49.979 --> 01:25:51.355
- Wow! That was quick!

01:25:51.480 --> 01:25:53.691
- I learned from the best.

01:25:57.528 --> 01:25:58.988
Shit!

01:25:59.321 --> 01:26:01.532
<i>- What?</i>
- My son! He tried to call me!

01:26:01.657 --> 01:26:04.743
<i>- Cool, that's a good sign!
I knew you'd work it out!</i>

01:26:05.327 --> 01:26:08.622
<i>- You assholes--</i>
(Mike grunting, dog barking)

01:26:10.166 --> 01:26:14.044
- So, tell us everything you know right now,

01:26:14.170 --> 01:26:16.672
and we might be willing to deal.

01:26:17.298 --> 01:26:21.135
<i>- You can shove your deals up your ass!</i>

01:26:21.260 --> 01:26:22.469
(Chuckling)

01:26:24.096 --> 01:26:25.639
<i>- I know you, Mike.</i>

01:26:26.765 --> 01:26:29.393
<i>You're a liar, a thief and a cheat.</i>

01:26:29.518 --> 01:26:31.061
<i>All about cash and chicks.</i>

01:26:32.563 --> 01:26:33.647
<i>But you're no killer.</i>

01:26:33.772 --> 01:26:36.233
- Money has that effect on certain people.

01:26:36.358 --> 01:26:38.527
<i>- You think I'm scared of the police?</i>

01:26:38.903 --> 01:26:41.614
<i>You gonna hit me with a phonebook
if I don't talk?</i>

01:26:45.451 --> 01:26:46.911
- Hey.

01:26:47.995 --> 01:26:52.666
<i>Look around, you moron.
Does this look like a police station?</i>

01:26:53.167 --> 01:26:55.461
<i>You think we brought you here to finger paint</i>

01:26:55.586 --> 01:26:58.130
<i>and take pictures of your ugly face?</i>

01:27:00.424 --> 01:27:01.926
<i>I'll rearrange your face!</i>

01:27:03.594 --> 01:27:05.095
Shit! Fuck!

01:27:05.221 --> 01:27:07.056
<i>My wife!</i>

01:27:07.556 --> 01:27:09.808
- What?
<i>- It's my wife!</i>

01:27:09.934 --> 01:27:11.268
(Grunting)

01:27:11.936 --> 01:27:13.437
<i>Hide him! Hide him!</i>

01:27:19.443 --> 01:27:22.029
<i>- David?
- Hello!</i>

01:27:22.738 --> 01:27:24.448
<i>Did I wake you?</i>

01:27:24.573 --> 01:27:26.033
(Sighing)

01:27:26.158 --> 01:27:27.660
<i>- It doesn't matter.</i>

01:27:28.160 --> 01:27:30.204
<i>What are you doing?</i>
(Muttering)

01:27:31.455 --> 01:27:32.456
<i>- Working.</i>

01:27:33.832 --> 01:27:35.167
(Clearing throat)

01:27:35.292 --> 01:27:37.920
<i>- You have blood on your hand.</i>
- Huh?

01:27:39.922 --> 01:27:41.882
<i>Oh, yeah! Would you look at that!</i>

01:27:43.425 --> 01:27:44.468
(Grunting)

01:27:47.471 --> 01:27:50.015
<i>- Is someone with you?
- No.</i>

01:27:51.016 --> 01:27:52.643
<i>Oh, him? That's just Martin.</i>

01:27:53.227 --> 01:27:55.062
<i>- Martin! Well, I--</i>

01:27:56.105 --> 01:27:58.482
<i>- My love, you can't go in the garage.</i>

01:27:59.858 --> 01:28:03.904
<i>- You'd better not be putting us
in danger with your bullshit.</i>

01:28:04.822 --> 01:28:05.990
<i>- No way!</i>

01:28:07.157 --> 01:28:08.867
<i>Trust me!</i>

01:28:08.993 --> 01:28:10.077
(Sighing)

01:28:11.704 --> 01:28:13.622
<i>- We'll talk about this later.</i>

01:28:13.747 --> 01:28:14.915
- OK.

01:28:15.249 --> 01:28:17.668
<i>Thank you, my love! I love you!</i>

01:28:29.930 --> 01:28:32.099
<i>I'm in big trouble.</i>

01:28:32.224 --> 01:28:34.518
- She's crazy about you.

01:28:34.643 --> 01:28:35.853
Lucky prick!

01:28:37.313 --> 01:28:38.314
(Mike): Aaah!

01:28:38.439 --> 01:28:40.190
- Oh, shit!

01:28:48.449 --> 01:28:49.908
(Wheezing)

01:28:54.246 --> 01:28:56.081
<i>- Come on, Michel!</i>

01:28:57.624 --> 01:28:59.209
(Breathing heavily)

01:28:59.335 --> 01:29:02.212
<i>Don't swallow this! It's bad for your health!</i>
(Coughing)

01:29:02.338 --> 01:29:06.258
<i>- I know where you live!
I'll slit your wife's throat!</i>

01:29:06.592 --> 01:29:08.427
- What did you say?

01:29:08.552 --> 01:29:11.638
Listen! You tell me what I need
to know right now, or I'll--

01:29:11.764 --> 01:29:15.559
- Or what? <i>You think I'm scared
of a few punches in the face?</i>

01:29:18.062 --> 01:29:22.441
- Listen to me,
you worthless speck of dog shit!

01:29:22.566 --> 01:29:24.777
My wife is gone, my son won't talk to me,

01:29:24.902 --> 01:29:25.861
and I'm dying.

01:29:25.986 --> 01:29:28.030
So if you think I give a flying fuck

01:29:28.155 --> 01:29:30.407
whether you die tonight, think again!

01:29:30.532 --> 01:29:34.661
You know when they say this guy did this crazy thing
because he had nothing to lose?

01:29:34.787 --> 01:29:36.705
Well, I'm that fucking guy! OK?

01:29:36.830 --> 01:29:38.248
(Whimpering)

01:29:42.711 --> 01:29:45.672
You tell me where this thing
is going down right now,

01:29:45.798 --> 01:29:48.801
or I will drill so many holes
in your hideous face

01:29:48.926 --> 01:29:50.219
that when the sun rises

01:29:50.344 --> 01:29:52.930
and the beams shine through
your ugly fucking skull,

01:29:53.055 --> 01:29:55.432
you will light up
like a goddamn disco ball!

01:29:55.557 --> 01:29:58.560
<i>- OK, OK, OK! But it's too late!</i>

01:29:58.685 --> 01:30:00.270
<i>There are already 20 cars across the border.</i>

01:30:00.396 --> 01:30:02.815
<i>The last batch leaves this morning.</i>

01:30:02.940 --> 01:30:05.692
<i>They're all rigged to explode on the same day!</i>

01:30:05.818 --> 01:30:08.362
<i>They're mobile bombs! That's it!</i>

01:30:08.487 --> 01:30:09.863
<i>- Who's delivering the cars?</i>

01:30:10.781 --> 01:30:13.659
<i>- A bunch of greedy kids. But they won't be back.</i>

01:30:13.784 --> 01:30:18.205
<i>They don't know the cars are rigged.
They're going to explode with them.</i>

01:30:18.330 --> 01:30:20.290
<i>There's no connection between them.</i>

01:30:20.416 --> 01:30:23.710
<i>By the time the FBI figures it out,
everyone will be gone.</i>

01:30:23.836 --> 01:30:25.170
- Where are the computers?

01:30:25.295 --> 01:30:27.965
<i>- I don't know. I swear I don't know!</i>

01:30:28.090 --> 01:30:30.676
<i>All we did was get the cars
and handle delivery.</i>

01:30:30.801 --> 01:30:33.470
<i>I don't even know
when they're set to go off!</i>

01:30:34.179 --> 01:30:38.392
<i>All I know is the last batch
is leaving this morning at 5:00!</i>

01:30:38.517 --> 01:30:40.644
<i>- From where?</i>
- Huh?

01:30:40.769 --> 01:30:45.732
<i>- From where?
- A vacant lot in the east end!</i>

01:30:45.858 --> 01:30:48.485
<i>That's all I know, I swear!</i>

01:30:48.610 --> 01:30:50.154
(Sobbing)

01:30:59.288 --> 01:31:00.956
(Breathing heavily)

01:31:04.084 --> 01:31:06.712
- Did I make him talk or what?

01:31:07.880 --> 01:31:12.885
<i>- Impressive. Especially using
a drill with no battery.</i>

01:31:17.598 --> 01:31:19.433
(Both chuckling)

01:31:22.561 --> 01:31:24.396
- Michel!

01:31:24.521 --> 01:31:26.356
There's no fucking battery!

01:31:26.482 --> 01:31:29.568
<i>- Don't call me Michel!</i>

01:31:33.572 --> 01:31:35.032
(Gun cocking)

01:31:38.285 --> 01:31:39.828
<i>- You sure you're OK with this?</i>

01:31:39.953 --> 01:31:42.164
- No choice. No time to go for more help.

01:31:42.289 --> 01:31:44.374
<i>- It might not go that far.</i>

01:31:58.180 --> 01:32:01.308
<i>If plan A doesn't work,
we go right to plan B. Got it?</i>

01:32:01.433 --> 01:32:03.602
<i>- Sounds to me like you have two plan Cs!</i>

01:32:03.727 --> 01:32:08.065
<i>- Well, well! The strip-club owner
is suddenly a mastermind!</i>

01:32:09.608 --> 01:32:11.443
<i>Get over your fear of harmless tools</i>

01:32:11.568 --> 01:32:14.947
<i>and then apply for a job with the RCMP or the SQ!</i>

01:32:16.073 --> 01:32:18.116
<i>Handcuffs?</i>

01:32:21.870 --> 01:32:23.497
<i>But if you're shaking like that...</i>

01:32:23.622 --> 01:32:25.499
- I'll be fine. Don't worry.

01:32:25.624 --> 01:32:29.002
- You have your meds?
Now would be a good time to take them.

01:32:29.127 --> 01:32:31.296
And if you have any extras...

01:32:33.590 --> 01:32:36.134
- Give me 90 seconds. I'll be in place.

01:32:37.010 --> 01:32:40.806
<i>- Well, Michel, our lives are connected.</i>

01:32:41.974 --> 01:32:43.934
<i>If something happens, we're both dead.</i>

01:32:44.518 --> 01:32:46.353
<i>- You guys are fucking nuts.</i>

01:32:47.271 --> 01:32:51.149
<i>- That's the nicest thing
you've ever said to me. Thank you.</i>

01:32:51.900 --> 01:32:53.902
<i>Let's go.</i>

01:33:17.426 --> 01:33:19.177
<i>Martin, are you ready?</i>

01:33:20.470 --> 01:33:22.556
(Men talking, indistinct)

01:33:33.400 --> 01:33:35.777
(Over earpiece): <i>I'm coming in. 2 o'clock.</i>

01:33:39.656 --> 01:33:40.699
Hey!

01:33:43.660 --> 01:33:45.996
<i>I found your poodle. Is there a reward?</i>

01:33:48.373 --> 01:33:49.833
- Get in your fucking cars! Go!

01:33:49.958 --> 01:33:52.210
- Shit! David, are you hit?

01:33:52.336 --> 01:33:54.004
<i>- What a shitty plan!</i>

01:33:54.129 --> 01:33:55.255
<i>The cars can't go.</i>

01:33:57.883 --> 01:33:58.967
(Screaming)

01:34:01.386 --> 01:34:02.721
(Grunting)

01:34:26.662 --> 01:34:28.705
- Aaah!

01:34:32.250 --> 01:34:35.295
- Jonathan! Jonathan!

01:34:39.758 --> 01:34:41.301
- Drop the fucking gun!

01:34:41.426 --> 01:34:43.887
(Screaming)

01:34:44.012 --> 01:34:45.430
(Tires screeching)

01:34:45.555 --> 01:34:46.556
Martin!

01:34:46.682 --> 01:34:50.435
<i>- Hey, you've reached Jonathan.
You know what to do after the beep.</i>

01:34:50.560 --> 01:34:52.938
(Whispering): Come on!

01:34:55.524 --> 01:34:58.068
- Martin! Martin!

01:34:58.485 --> 01:35:00.070
<i>Martin, I've got DiPietro!</i>

01:35:01.029 --> 01:35:04.908
<i>Martin, where are you? Can you hear me?</i>

01:35:06.952 --> 01:35:07.953
(Groaning)

01:35:08.078 --> 01:35:09.830
<i>I need help with the kids!</i>

01:35:09.955 --> 01:35:11.373
(Moaning)

01:35:11.707 --> 01:35:14.459
<i>This will hurt, but you need
to put direct pressure on it.</i>

01:35:14.584 --> 01:35:16.044
(Beeping)
<i>- Ostie de c--</i>

01:35:17.254 --> 01:35:18.213
- Fuck!

01:35:20.340 --> 01:35:23.760
<i>Martin, they can see us! It's going to blow!</i>

01:35:26.722 --> 01:35:28.306
Calice!

01:35:28.432 --> 01:35:30.267
- Shut up! Shut up!

01:35:53.915 --> 01:35:55.125
(Metal creaking)

01:35:57.753 --> 01:35:59.463
<i>- TABARNAK!</i>

01:36:24.988 --> 01:36:26.490
<i>What the fuck?</i>

01:36:27.783 --> 01:36:29.201
(Laughing)

01:36:35.749 --> 01:36:36.875
Martin!

01:36:38.001 --> 01:36:39.419
Martin!

01:36:39.544 --> 01:36:41.922
- My son is one of the drivers.

01:36:43.173 --> 01:36:44.174
<i>- What?</i>

01:36:45.759 --> 01:36:49.012
- My son is driving one of those cars.

01:36:54.893 --> 01:36:58.104
- Martin! Martin!

01:36:58.230 --> 01:37:01.066
- He called. I could've saved him.

01:37:01.942 --> 01:37:03.568
<i>- Get a hold of yourself!</i>

01:37:03.693 --> 01:37:06.279
- I could've saved him.
Now my son is gone because of me.

01:37:06.822 --> 01:37:10.659
<i>- Martin, I understand, but this isn't the time!</i>
- I killed my son.

01:37:10.784 --> 01:37:12.369
- Huh?
- I killed him.

01:37:12.494 --> 01:37:13.787
- No! No!

01:37:13.912 --> 01:37:15.205
(Sniffling)

01:37:15.330 --> 01:37:17.332
Hey! Hey, shake it off, man!

01:37:17.457 --> 01:37:18.750
(Siren wailing)

01:37:18.875 --> 01:37:20.335
He's not dead!

01:37:20.460 --> 01:37:23.964
<i>He's not dead!
There weren't any other explosions!</i>

01:37:24.089 --> 01:37:26.049
<i>But I need you now!</i>

01:37:26.174 --> 01:37:27.843
<i>Jonathan needs you!</i>

01:37:31.304 --> 01:37:32.722
- Let's find him.

01:37:32.848 --> 01:37:34.432
What are you doing? Let's go!

01:37:34.558 --> 01:37:36.059
<i>- We can't go after your son.</i>

01:37:36.184 --> 01:37:40.647
- What? Let go of me!
<i>- Penses-y.</i> Think about it.

01:37:40.772 --> 01:37:42.774
- I don't wanna save the world.
I just wanna save my son!

01:37:42.899 --> 01:37:46.903
<i>- Me too! But we won't find your son
before he crosses the border.</i>

01:37:47.028 --> 01:37:51.575
<i>The only way to save your son
is to stop the cars from exploding.</i>

01:37:53.118 --> 01:37:55.412
- OK. OK.

01:38:08.466 --> 01:38:10.927
- Everything's ready. We need to move.

01:38:12.429 --> 01:38:14.681
- Take a deep breath and relax, kid.

01:38:16.641 --> 01:38:19.978
We are gonna stick to the schedule
exactly as planned.

01:38:20.103 --> 01:38:21.938
Now, what happened this morning

01:38:22.063 --> 01:38:25.025
was just a little bump on the road.

01:38:25.150 --> 01:38:28.028
We still have 27 cars in play

01:38:28.153 --> 01:38:32.282
and nobody has a clue
about what is about to go down.

01:38:33.366 --> 01:38:34.284
(Exhaling sharply)

01:38:42.792 --> 01:38:44.085
(Exhaling sharply)

01:38:45.962 --> 01:38:48.173
Today, we write history.

01:38:48.298 --> 01:38:52.385
See, the fight for freedom
is a never-ending fight

01:38:52.510 --> 01:38:54.387
that demands sacrifice.

01:38:54.512 --> 01:38:57.974
And it is worthy of everything we got.

01:38:58.099 --> 01:39:02.062
If our neighbours are poor or defenceless,

01:39:02.187 --> 01:39:04.105
it is our duty to protect them,

01:39:04.230 --> 01:39:06.358
sometimes even against themselves.

01:39:06.483 --> 01:39:08.151
Our country,

01:39:08.276 --> 01:39:11.446
our brothers and sisters are stoned:

01:39:11.571 --> 01:39:13.281
stoned on comfort,

01:39:13.406 --> 01:39:16.409
stoned on pumpkin-spice lattes

01:39:16.534 --> 01:39:18.578
and fucking Facebook!

01:39:19.788 --> 01:39:22.749
Somebody needs to step up and save them.

01:39:22.874 --> 01:39:25.585
Not friend them. Save them.

01:39:26.711 --> 01:39:28.505
And that somebody is us.

01:39:31.174 --> 01:39:32.467
Do you know why?

01:39:34.511 --> 01:39:38.390
Because we are the true patriots.

01:39:40.642 --> 01:39:42.644
And if we succeed today,

01:39:42.769 --> 01:39:47.315
50 years from now... we'll be in every textbook.

01:39:48.483 --> 01:39:50.151
But if we fail...

01:39:52.487 --> 01:39:53.863
Shit!

01:39:53.989 --> 01:39:56.032
Those pricks don't give up!

01:39:56.157 --> 01:39:57.033
- What is it?

01:39:57.158 --> 01:39:59.202
- Fucking Canadian cops!

01:39:59.327 --> 01:40:00.412
Ali, Connor,

01:40:00.537 --> 01:40:03.248
go and do everything exactly as we planned.

01:40:03.373 --> 01:40:04.624
- Yes, sir!

01:40:04.749 --> 01:40:06.626
- You, come with me.

01:40:06.751 --> 01:40:10.714
- Sir, I wanna be a part of--
- Shut up! Don't question my orders.

01:40:10.839 --> 01:40:12.549
- No papers, no numbers today.

01:40:12.674 --> 01:40:14.217
I wanna speak to your boss.

01:40:14.342 --> 01:40:17.262
- It's protocol. You need an appointment.

01:40:17.387 --> 01:40:20.890
<i>- What part of "emergency"
don't you understand?</i>

01:40:21.016 --> 01:40:23.435
- Sir, lower your voice!

01:40:25.353 --> 01:40:26.730
(Men and women screaming)

01:40:28.857 --> 01:40:31.234
- We need to talk to the person in charge, <i>bâtard!</i>

01:40:31.359 --> 01:40:32.736
- Get down!

01:40:32.861 --> 01:40:33.862
<i>- Bon!</i>

01:40:33.987 --> 01:40:35.488
- Get down on your knees!

01:40:35.613 --> 01:40:38.324
<i>- Are they going to take us seriously now?</i>

01:40:38.450 --> 01:40:39.826
- Down on your knees!

01:40:40.452 --> 01:40:43.288
<i>- I can't take their shitty attitude anymore!</i>

01:40:43.747 --> 01:40:46.458
<i>You're lucky my friend's son
is caught up in this,</i>

01:40:46.583 --> 01:40:50.128
<i>otherwise I'd be at home
with my feet up, drinking a beer</i>

01:40:50.253 --> 01:40:54.257
<i>and watching the cars blow up live
on fucking CNN!</i>

01:40:54.382 --> 01:40:58.553
<i>I can't handle them acting
like they're king of the world,</i>

01:40:58.678 --> 01:41:01.347
<i>as if the Garden of Eden itself
was in sunny California!</i>

01:41:01.473 --> 01:41:04.601
- FBI! Everybody put your guns down!

01:41:04.726 --> 01:41:06.102
Put them down!

01:41:06.227 --> 01:41:08.146
(Alarm sounding)

01:41:08.271 --> 01:41:10.023
Put them down.

01:41:11.066 --> 01:41:14.152
I know these men.
They are Canadian police officers.

01:41:14.277 --> 01:41:15.695
They're working with us.

01:41:18.114 --> 01:41:20.950
Gentlemen! If you would please come with me.

01:41:22.243 --> 01:41:23.953
I was just about to call you.

01:41:27.290 --> 01:41:31.252
<i>- Sometimes you have to be direct
in order to get things moving.</i>

01:41:31.377 --> 01:41:33.213
Hi, I'm David.

01:41:35.507 --> 01:41:38.718
- Gentlemen, after our little misadventure
up in Maine,

01:41:38.843 --> 01:41:42.514
I decided to come down here
and check things out for myself.

01:41:42.639 --> 01:41:44.724
Turns out, you were right.

01:41:45.642 --> 01:41:48.895
That man in there
was planning a terrorist attack on American soil.

01:41:50.605 --> 01:41:52.565
But we have him now, thanks to you.

01:41:52.690 --> 01:41:54.317
And I am gonna see to it,

01:41:54.442 --> 01:41:58.071
and I'm gonna make sure
that the proper authorities know

01:41:58.196 --> 01:42:00.240
what you both have done for my country.

01:42:00.365 --> 01:42:02.158
- But there are at least 3 of them.

01:42:02.283 --> 01:42:05.245
- Yes. The other two are also in custody.

01:42:05.370 --> 01:42:07.997
We've also impounded their cars and their computers.

01:42:08.123 --> 01:42:10.416
- And you were able to locate all of the cars?

01:42:10.542 --> 01:42:11.876
- Most of them.

01:42:12.001 --> 01:42:14.546
It's only a matter of time before we get them all.

01:42:17.632 --> 01:42:18.675
- It's over?

01:42:18.800 --> 01:42:20.093
- Yes.

01:42:21.928 --> 01:42:23.763
It's done.

01:42:27.183 --> 01:42:28.268
- It's over.

01:42:28.393 --> 01:42:31.855
<i>- Martin, David, can you hear me?
I picked up the signal!</i>

01:42:32.230 --> 01:42:35.525
- I'm sorry. I'm gonna have to take this.

01:42:35.650 --> 01:42:36.860
- Of course.

01:42:36.985 --> 01:42:38.528
- Yes, MC?

01:42:38.653 --> 01:42:41.614
<i>- I've got their computer's signal!
They reconnected!</i>

01:42:42.240 --> 01:42:44.742
- Slow down. Explain this to me again.

